==English==
===Etymology===
From {{Arab.}} ثعبان , "the [[basilisk]]", which is the Arabic name for the constellation [[Draco]].

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Thuban}}
'''Thuban'''

#{{star}}: A white [[giant]] [[star]] in the [[constellation]] [[Draco]]; Alpha (α) Draconis. It was the [[pole star]] 5000 years ago.

